<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880126-0164 </DOCNO><HL> Allegheny International Unit </HL><SO> </SO><CO> AG </CO><IN> TNM </IN><DATELINE> PITTSBURGH  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Allegheny International Inc. said its Thermco Systems Inc. subsidiary sold its 50% interest in Tel-Thermco Engineering Co. to Tokyo Electron Ltd., its partner in the 20-year-old venture. Terms weren't announced.    Tel-Thermco, based in California, makes systems used in the thermal processing of silicon wafers. Allegheny International said the sale of its unit's 50% interest is in line with its divestiture program to focus on North American consumer products. </TEXT></DOC>